 The accident took place on the R555 (old Witbank Road) at around 05:25, when a Toyota Hilux and Isuzu bakkie collided head on. One of the passengers from the Isuzu was killed upon impact and the two drivers were rushed to Life Midmed Hospital in critical condition.
It was later confirmed that one of the two drivers has succumbed to their injuries in hospital. This brings the death toll to fourteen fatalities in four days. The road had to be closed as rescuers recovered the deceased’s body from one of the wreckages. •The R555 is now open for use.     The ferals need help #TrafficAlert: R555 closed, seven die in horrific crash Middelburg police officer arrested during Hawks operation  • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za